data.reasoningText:
Now I have a good understanding of the project. Let me plan the component decomposition and implement it.

## Component Plan: Settings Dashboard

### Component Tree
```
SettingsPage                    (page — route /settings, owns active section + all data)
├── SettingsSidebar             (vertical nav tabs)
├── ProfileSection              (profile editing form)
├── NotificationsSection        (notification preferences)
├── SecuritySection             (security settings)
│   ├── ChangePasswordPanel     (expandable password change form)
│   └── RevokeSessionDialog     (confirmation modal)
└── AppearanceSection           (appearance settings with live preview)


```

The SettingsPage component will manage the active section state and hold all the loaded data, passing it down to each section along with the necessary callbacks. The SecuritySection will handle its own internal state for the password form and session revocation flow. I'll start by creating the models and service interface, then build the leaf components before composing them into the larger sections.

I'm going to batch create all the Razor components using Bootstrap styling. The namespace will be `sv_5ba01906ffcc4ef982fa258272d7d044`, and I need to set up the models file, sidebar, dialog panels, individual sections, the main SettingsPage component, and register everything in dependency injection.

```

csharp
// Models.cs
namespace sv_5ba01906ffcc4ef982fa258272d7d044.Models
{
    public record UserProfile(string Username, string Email, string FullName, DateTime CreatedDate);

